# Post-Implementation Playtest

After finishing a feature implementation (code changes complete, no linter errors), **always** start the game in Roblox Studio using the MCP.

## Steps

1. Call `list_roblox_studios` to confirm the active studio.
2. Call `start_stop_play` with `{"is_start": true}` to run the game.
3. If the feature is **arena-only** (combat HUD, in-match UI, weapon behavior, round mechanics, etc.), also navigate the character to an arena pad using `character_navigation` to `game.Workspace.Lobby.SpawnPads.BluePad` with `speed_multiplier: 2`.
4. Stop there. The user will take over for manual testing.

Do **not** run the full shop/loadout/playtest flow. Do **not** click UI or interact with prompts. Just start the game and optionally move to the pad.
